 \centerline {\bf On one very beautiful formula}

  (Written under impression of the article:of Passare.)


  Let $AB$ be a segmentof unit length. For any point $C$ on the
  plane one can consider coordinates $(u,v)$ or $(\a,\beta)$ where
           $$
      |CA|=e^{-u}, |CA|=e^{-v}
           $$
and respectively
         $$
\a=\angle CAB
         $$
